==English==

===Etymology===
:1879, German: ''Antisemitismus'', coined by German political agitator [[w:Wilhelm Marr|Wilhelm Marr]] to replace ''Judenhass'', making hatred of the Jews seem rational and sanctioned by scientific knowledge.  Similar term ''antisemitisch'' (anti-semitic) dates from 1860, by Jewish scholar [[w:Moritz Steinschneider|Moritz Steinschneider]].  See Wikipedia: [[w: Antisemitism#Etymology and usage|Antisemitism:Etymology and Usage]]

